# Documentation & Scope Discipline

## Always update docs when architecture changes
The documentation in `docs/` is part of the product. When you change architecture,
services, data models, agents, or workflows, update the relevant doc(s) in the same
change. A feature is not "done" if the docs are stale.

## Stay in scope
- Do not modify unrelated files. Touch only what the task requires.
- Prefer additive changes; avoid sweeping refactors unless the task asks for them.
- If you notice an unrelated bug, note it in your summary instead of fixing it silently.

## Verification is mandatory
Every meaningful change must ship with **exact, copy-pasteable verification steps**
(how to run it, what to look for). See [`docs/12-verification-guide.md`](../../docs/12-verification-guide.md).
